Spanish artist Frida Kahlo wrote passionate letters to Jose Bartoli from 1946 and 1949 while she was recovering from surgery in New York .
The letters, written in Spanish between August 1946 and November 1949, are expected to fetch upwards of $120,000 at auction later this month .
A collection of 25 of the letters will be auctioned off at Doyle New York on April 15 .